kubectl delete deployment superset keycloak redis postgres
kubectl delete service superset keycloak redis postgres
Or if you want to delete everything at once from your manifest files:
powershellkubectl delete -f env-configmap.yaml
kubectl delete -f superset-config.yaml
kubectl delete -f keycloak.yaml
kubectl delete -f superset.yaml
kubectl delete -f redis.yaml
kubectl delete -f postgres.yaml

And to bring everything back up:
powershell
kubectl apply -f configmap.yaml
kubectl apply -f superset-config.yaml
kubectl apply -f keycloak.yaml
kubectl apply -f superset.yaml
kubectl apply -f redis.yaml
kubectl apply -f postgres.yaml


